<html><hr><head><h2>Editor's Note</h2></head>
<p><hr>
<body><h4>
In the Fall 1995 issue of the <i>OCRWM Bulletin</i>, OCRWM ran an
article titled "Regulatory Drop Tests Planned for a Model
Transportation Cask." The article should have noted that
Precision Components Corporation (PCC) of York, Pennsylvania, a
subcontractor to General Atomics, fabricated the GA-4 half-scale
cask model discussed and pictured in the article.
<p>
Our apologies to PCC.</h4></body></html>
